<text>Loading models from a pulldown list

&lt;  Index  &gt;

This functionality is now deprecated. Please use a combo box in conjunction with the load command instead.

If you have multiple models which you would like the users to compare, there are three ways to put them in your activity:

   Put them on the same page, using two model containers. (If there are two models.)
   Put each model on a separate page.
   Put the models in a pulldown list.

In this section, we will show you how to set up a pulldown list (also known as combo box or drop down list) that will load models into a model container. Before we start, let us see how this works. The following is a model container with a pulldown list on top.

